Potential notes/slides for CEP146 Project
AI in healthcare:
-Sepsis is one of the leading causes of death in hospitals
-It is a life-threathening condition that occurs when the body’s immune response to an infection leads to widespread inflammation and organ dysfunction.
-Sepsis, when detected early, is relatively cheap and easy to treat (antibiotics and fluids are cheap and available).
-AI can work in real time, pulling live data, and recognize data and patterns that lead to sepsis. Which in turn can save lives

AI use and epilepsy
-AI can be used to read electrical brainwave recordings and recognize subtle patterns, used to detect epilepsy

Conclusion:
-AI should be used to compliment human intelligence, not replace it, so that healthcare professionals can make a more accurate and 
informed final decision regarding treatment.
